genresAdvancedInfo.name: scottish fiddle
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Scottish fiddle music is a traditional style of music that originated in Scotland. It is characterized by its use of the fiddle as the primary instrument, as well as its lively and energetic rhythms. Scottish fiddle music often features dance tunes such as reels and jigs, as well as slower ballads and laments. It has a rich history and is still an important part of Scottish cultural heritage today.
